# Unit — Project Rules

## Tech stack

- **Language**: Swift 6.0 (strict concurrency; no @unchecked unless justified).
- **UI**: SwiftUI with NavigationStack architecture.
- **Persistence**: SwiftData. Local-first; schema designed for future CloudKit sync.
- **Target**: iOS 18+ (use Live Activities for rest timer).
- **Project layout**: App, Models, Views, Features (Workout, Templates, History), Services/Persistence, Resources.

## Data model (SwiftData)

- **Exercise**: id (UUID), displayName, aliases ([String]), notes, isBodyweight (Bool).
- **DayTemplate**: id, name, orderedExerciseIds ([UUID]), lastPerformedDate (optional).
- **WorkoutSession**: id, date, templateId, isCompleted, cycleId (optional), weekNumber.
- **SetEntry**: id, sessionId, exerciseId, weight (Double), reps (Int), rpe (Double 1–10), isWarmup (Bool), isCompleted (Bool), setIndex (Int).
- Use @Relationship / inverse where useful (e.g. Session → SetEntries). Register all model types in ModelContainer schema.

## Gym Test

- **Goal**: User can log one set (weight, reps, optional RPE, warmup) in **under 3 seconds** under physical stress.
- **Implied**: Default next set to last weight/reps (and last RPE). One primary CTA to complete set. Large tap targets. Optional RPE (picker 1–10), not required. No multi-step set entry. Rest timer accessible in-flow and on Lock Screen (Live Activity).

